```

Output ONLY the Python script. No prose, no markdown fences, no explanations.

## Sweep/Fan-In Input Handling:

When a node receives input from a sweep (parallel) node, the input will be a
**JSON array** (one element per sweep iteration), NOT a single value.

The environment variable `_sweep_keys` contains the original sweep parameter
values as a JSON array. Use it to correlate keys with computed results:

```python
import json, os
energies = json.loads(open("/mf/input/I1").read())    # e.g. [-1.167, -1.172, ...]
distances = json.loads(os.environ["_sweep_keys"])      # e.g. [0.5, 0.74, ...]
results = list(zip(distances, energies))
```

Always handle both sweep (JSON array) and non-sweep (single value) inputs.
